Sentencas: We consider a system of nonlinear PDEs in a domain with a triple phase boundary, describing electrochemical processes in a mixed conduction, solid-oxide cathode of a fuel cell.
Titulo: Reviewing the mathematical validity of a fuel cell cathode model. Existence of weak bounded solution

Sentencas: It represents oxygen diffusion (with nonlinear diffusion coefficient) in the gas phase, oxygen ion diffusion in the bulk phase, electron diffusion in the electrolyte, surface exchange (nonlinear) on the interface of gas and the (mixed conduction) electrode material and finally charge transfer (nonlinear) at the interface between the electrolyte and the electrode material.
Titulo: Reviewing the mathematical validity of a fuel cell cathode model. Existence of weak bounded solution

Sentencas: We prove the validity of the model both mathematically and numerically.
Titulo: Reviewing the mathematical validity of a fuel cell cathode model. Existence of weak bounded solution

Sentencas: In fact, we prove the existence of a bounded weak solution using the Schauder fixed point theorem.
Titulo: Reviewing the mathematical validity of a fuel cell cathode model. Existence of weak bounded solution

Sentencas: We calculate the numerical solutions for given function and parameter values, and show that they correspond to theoretical results.
Titulo: Reviewing the mathematical validity of a fuel cell cathode model. Existence of weak bounded solution

Sentencas: In particular, we provide a numerical confirmation of the a priori bounds.
Titulo: Reviewing the mathematical validity of a fuel cell cathode model. Existence of weak bounded solution
